rdf:Description.lla:note: Note reads: "This man was washed overboard and drowned after. Statement in Log Book and Depositions of the Crew in the consulate".
Log Book: 1863-12-10 at 1pm "Gone on shore for water along with other seaman and as soon as the Boat lands he walked off and never seen and said nothing he had no clothes only what he had on"

Certificate no: 236448. This man, the Mate, appears at top pf list instead of Master. Accompanying letter to the Superintendent of the Sailors, Liverpool, explains that the Mate appears first because the Master was delayed prior to sailing.
Registry or Assignment of Indenture: 1862-08-20, Liverpool
